## Idea

The _TeichmÃ¼ller space_ $\mathcal{T}_{\Sigma}$ of a  ([[closed manifold|closed]]) 2-[[dimension|dimensional]] [[manifold]] $\Sigma$  is the [[moduli space of complex structures]] on $\Sigma$, where two complex structures are identified is they are taken into each other by a [[homeomorphism]] $\phi \colon \Sigma \to \Sigma$ which is [[isotopy|isotopic]] to the [[identity]]. 

Since the [[diffeomorphism]] class of  a [[closed manifold]] of dimension 2 is given by its [[genus]] $g\in \mathbb{Z}$, typically one speaks of the TeichmÃ¼ller space $\mathcal{T}_g$ for each $g$. More generally one considers $\Sigma$s equipped with $n$ punctures/[[boundary]] circle and then writes $\mathcal{T}_{g,n}$. 

TeichmÃ¼ller space is a [[covering space]] for the [[moduli space of curves]] over the complex numbers (see [below](#RelationToModuliStackOfCurves)). When also the singular [[nodal curve]] is included one speaks of the _[[augmented TeichmÃ¼ller space]]_ which in turn is a cover of the [[Deligne-Mumford compactification]] of the moduli space of complex curves.



## Properties

### Complex structure on TeichmÃ¼ller space
 {#ComplexStructureOnTeichmÃ¼llerSpace}

TeichmÃ¼ller space itself carries a [[complex structure]]. 

This was envisioned in ([TeichmÃ¼ller 44](#Teichmuller44)) and proven in ([Ahlfors 60](#Ahlford60), [Bers 60](#Bers60)).

Review includes ([Schumacher, section 2](#Schumacher))

### Relation to moduli stack of complex curves / Riemann surfaces
 {#RelationToModuliStackOfCurves}

Quotienting the space of complex structures on $\Sigma$ by _all_ [[homeomorphisms]] produces what is called the [[moduli space of curves]] (over the complex numbers). 
Closely related to the [[moduli space of conformal structures]] hence of  [[Riemann surfaces]]. 

Hence the Riemann moduli space is the [[orbifold quotient]] of TeichmÃ¼ller space by the [[mapping class group]] of $\Sigma$. See ([Hubbard-Koch 13](#HubbardKoch13)).



